# Guidelines for Prayers Modification and Verification

Please follow these guidelines whenever you create, edit, or remove prayers in the `app/assets/prayers/` directory.

## 1. File Structure and Versioning
- Save translation files inside the corresponding prayer folder: `app/assets/prayers/{prayer_id}/{language}_v{version}.md`.
- **Handling Variations:** Do not overwrite existing translation files if a different translation variant is introduced (e.g., Traditional vs. Modern English). Instead:
  - Create a new version file (e.g., `english_v2.md`).
  - Add a distinguishing `subtitle` in the frontmatter (e.g., `subtitle: "Ave Maria (Traditional)"` vs. `subtitle: "Ave Maria (Modern)"`).

## 2. Frontmatter and Metadata Requirements
Every prayer Markdown file must contain a YAML frontmatter block with the following fields:
- `category`: The category name (e.g., `"starter"`).
- `default_order`: A sorting index integer.
- `default_title`: The global default title.
- `title`: The localized title of the prayer.
- `subtitle`: Subtitle, e.g. the alternative title or translation type.
- `source_name`: The canonical name of the source.
- `source_url`: A secure HTTPS link (`https://...`) to the web page hosting the official text.

## 3. Formatting & Interlinear Tokenization
- **Interlinear Alignment:** Split the prayer text logically by clause or sentence.
- Wrap each segment in the `{text|id}` tokenization syntax.
- Ensure the **same segment IDs** (e.g. `prayerId_1`, `prayerId_2`) are used across **all language versions** of the prayer so they align perfectly in the comparative/interlinear UI.
- Example:
  - In `hail_mary/english_v1.md`: `{Hail, Mary, full of grace|hail_mary_1}, {the Lord is with thee|hail_mary_2}.`
  - In `hail_mary/latin_v1.md`: `{Ave Maria, gratia plena|hail_mary_1}, {Dominus tecum|hail_mary_2}.`

## 4. Preferred Sourcing Guidelines
- Source prayers from official Catholic repositories:
  - Vatican (vatican.va)
  - USCCB (usccb.org)
  - Universalis (universalis.com)
  - Preces Latinae (preces-latinae.org)
- If official repositories are unavailable, fall back to verified Wikipedia or other peer-reviewed catechetical reference sites.
- Every source URL must start with `https://`.

## 5. Traditional Chinese Pinyin Dictionary
- When adding or modifying Traditional Chinese translations, ensure all Chinese characters used have pinyin mappings in [app/assets/pinyin_dict.txt](file:///home/mweastwood/projects/TwelveStars/app/assets/pinyin_dict.txt).
- If any characters are missing, append them to the text file in the format: `char: pinyin`.

## 6. Verification and Testing Workflows
After making changes to any file in `app/assets/prayers/`, you **must** execute the following verification steps before committing:

1. **Rebuild the Database:** Compile the raw Markdown files into the JSON catalog:
   ```bash
   # Run from the app/ directory
   dart bin/assemble_db.dart
   ```
2. **Run Integrity Tests:** Ensure all JSON properties, pinyin mappings, and translation rules are satisfied:
   ```bash
   # Run from the app/ directory
   flutter test test/logic/prayers_test.dart
   ```
3. **Run Source Verification Tests:** Ensure all lines of the prayer match the fetched official source text:
   ```bash
   # Run from the app/ directory
   flutter test test/logic/source_verification_test.dart
   ```

## 7. Meta-Guidelines (Updating Rules)
- If you are asked to perform an action, apply a pattern, or make changes that are not covered by or deviate from these guidelines, you MUST ask the user if this rule file (`.agents/rules/prayers.mdc`) should be updated to incorporate the new instructions or criteria.

